column2:
in a miracle
of too many aspirin
glides from window

sleepless night a new
turkey feather falling just
second glass of wine

tadpoles wriggle
houses without a shepherd
tea in the middle

night Only white spots
memorial day weekend
floats in the water

only the wildest
refrigerator freezes
beach the only light

deep into the night
showers her mascara runs
for their teenaged
